<p>My goal is to rename all Greek-named files to English ones (just by changing the Greek characters to their respective English ones). This is my code:</p>  <pre><code>lettersmap = {"α"=&gt;"a"} puts lettersmap["α"]  Dir.foreach('.') do |file_name|   file_name = file_name.split('')   file_name.each do |letter|     puts lettersmap[letter]   end end end </code></pre>  <p>At <code>puts lettersmap["α"]</code>, it prints <code>a</code>. If I have a file named <code>α.txt</code>, it doesn't. I tried <code>letter.encoding(Encoding::UTF_8)</code> and <code>letter.force_encoding(Encoding::UTF_8)</code>; neither worked. How can I index <code>lettersmap</code> using Greek letters?</p>